## Key Findings (Task #851)

- NO significant clinical associations after FDR correction (12 tests, all q>0.1).
- Treatment: anti-TNF 43.8% vs 50.0% (p=0.77), immunomod 25% vs 41.2% (p=0.35), steroids 56.2% vs 44.1% (p=0.55), 5-ASA 37.5% vs 32.4% (p=0.76). Adalimumab 0% vs 17.6% (p=0.16, underpowered).
- Disease activity: HBI identical (2.04 vs 2.05, p=0.76). CRP 3.46 vs 1.54 (p=0.41). Surgery 37.5% vs 26.5% (p=0.51).
- Longitudinal variability (suggestive but FDR q=0.27): HBI SD 1.88 vs 1.36 (p=0.031), CRP SD 1.45 vs 0.01 (p=0.045). Subtype 0 may be more disease-fluctuant.
- Logistic regression AUC=0.581 — clinical features don't predict subtype.
- Calprotectin unavailable (column has tube IDs, not assay values).
- Subtypes are molecularly defined, not clinically distinguishable. Consistent with #850 (Montreal all p>0.3).

## Technical Notes

- API auth: X-API-Key header from .env. Medication columns encoded as "Current"/"Taken since last visit"/"Never taken"/"Taken prior to baseline" — NOT "Yes"/"No".
- HMP2 metadata: 5533 rows, 490 columns. 50 CD subjects, 2628 rows (median 52 timepoints/subject).
- Calprotectin (Tube B:Fecal Calprotectin) = sample tube IDs (SM-xxxxx), not assay values.
- Results saved: output/crohns/microbiome-metabolome-subtyping/clinical_relevance_results.json

